Package: AutoSULT
Version: 1.0-1
Date: 2020-04-28
Title: Automatic Mortality Table Problem Generation
Authors@R: person("Chris", "Groendyke", email = "groendyke@rmu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Chris Groendyke <groendyke@rmu.edu>
Description: Code to automatically generate selected types of problems and solutions from Chapters 3, 4, and 5 of Actuarial Mathematics for Life Contingent Risks, 2nd edition, by Dickson, Hardy, and Waters.  The problems generated make use of the Standard Ultimate Survival Model (SUSM) a.k.a. Standard Ultimate Life Table (SULT), a mortality table based on Makeham's law and defined on pg. 65 of AMLCR2e.  Problems and solutions are typeset in LaTeX and rendered to PDF files.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.6)
Imports:
    kableExtra (>= 1.1),
    knitr (>= 1.2),
    rmarkdown (>= 1.16),
    magrittr
LazyData: true
LazyLoad: yes
License: GPL-2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
